3. Thirdly, thinke that thou receiueſt him, who is the Holie of all Holies, & for that reſpect art to come vnto him;

                           〈2 pages missing〉



                        him ſelfe &c. Furthermore the cuſtome of the Church declareth, that this examination is moſt behoueful & neceſſarie, ſo that no man being in mortal ſinne, haue he neuer ſo great contrition, ought to preſume to come to the B. Sacrament, not firſt hauinge confeſſed his ſinnes to a lawful Prieſt.
